{"version": 2, "width": 110, "height": 42, "timestamp": 1711900000, "title": "DGE v2→v3: We DGE'd DGE", "env": {"SHELL": "/bin/bash", "TERM": "xterm-256color"}}
[0.0, "o", "\u001b[2J\u001b[H"]
[0.5, "o", "\u001b[1;37m━━━ DGE toolkit: v2 → v3 ━━━\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[1.0, "o", "\u001b[2m\"We DGE'd DGE — and it changed the architecture\"\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[2.5, "o", "\u001b[1;33m【Origin】\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[3.0, "o", "  While developing the parser framework unlaxer-parser,\r\n"]
[3.5, "o", "  the author generated \"review plays\" — fictional peer reviews\r\n"]
[4.2, "o", "  where 3 reviewers independently evaluated the paper and source code,\r\n"]
[4.9, "o", "  then characters argued and defended against those reviews.\r\n"]
[5.6, "o", "  \u001b[1m5 review plays found 108 gaps.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[6.3, "o", "  The author fell in love with the method.\r\n\r\n"]
[7.5, "o", "  \"Let's make this usable for everyone.\"\r\n"]
[8.0, "o", "  → DGE toolkit packaged as npm.\r\n"]
[8.5, "o", "  → 19 characters, templates, auto-iteration.\r\n\r\n"]
[9.5, "o", "\u001b[1;31m【The Problem】\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[10.0, "o", "  But the npm version didn't produce gaps as deep as the review plays.\r\n"]
[10.7, "o", "  Characters were fun. Dialogues were entertaining.\r\n"]
[11.4, "o", "  \u001b[1mBut \"I never thought of that\" moments were rare.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[12.1, "o", "  The review plays had them every time.\r\n\r\n"]
[13.1, "o", "  \u001b[2mWhy? What was different between review plays and standard DGE?\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[14.5, "o", "\u001b[1;37m━━━ Analysis: We ran DGE on DGE ━━━\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[15.5, "o", "\u001b[1;32m>\u001b[0m run DGE on DGE-toolkit's user experience\r\n\r\n"]
[16.3, "o", "  5 rounds, 8 characters.\r\n"]
[16.8, "o", "  \u001b[1;32m✓ 33 gaps (Critical: 2, High: 11)\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[17.8, "o", "  Then we ran DGE on \"why do review plays work?\"\r\n"]
[18.3, "o", "  \u001b[1;32m✓ 31 gaps (Critical: 9, High: 19)\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[19.5, "o", "\u001b[1;33m【Discovery】The review play success formula\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[20.5, "o", "  \u001b[1m1. Input density\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[21.0, "o", "     Review plays: paper + source code = thousands of lines\r\n"]
[21.5, "o", "     Standard DGE: \"run DGE on the auth API\" = 1 line\r\n"]
[22.0, "o", "     → \u001b[1;31m1000x density gap. Characters were guessing.\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[23.0, "o", "  \u001b[1m2. Format enforcement\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[23.5, "o", "     Review plays: Summary / Strengths / Weaknesses / Questions / Verdict\r\n"]
[24.0, "o", "     Standard DGE: free conversation. Characters only hit their strengths\r\n"]
[24.5, "o", "     → \u001b[1;31mNo coverage guarantee.\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[25.5, "o", "  \u001b[1m3. Response obligation\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[26.0, "o", "     Review plays: characters must rebut every point. No escape\r\n"]
[26.5, "o", "     Standard DGE: drive-by critiques. No one responds\r\n"]
[27.0, "o", "     → \u001b[1;31mDiscussion never went deep.\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[28.0, "o", "  \u001b[1m4. Explicit evaluation axis\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[28.5, "o", "     Review plays: evaluated on \"novelty\", \"correctness\", \"practicality\"\r\n"]
[29.0, "o", "     Standard DGE: characters had personality but no judgment criteria\r\n"]
[29.5, "o", "     → \u001b[1;31mUnclear what they were evaluating against.\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[31.0, "o", "\u001b[1;37m━━━ v3.0.0: Four changes ━━━\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[32.0, "o", "  \u001b[1;36m① Phase 0 — Auto-collect project context\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[32.5, "o", "    README, docs/, tree, package.json, git log — automatic\r\n"]
[33.0, "o", "    → Characters argue from facts, not guesses\r\n\r\n"]
[33.8, "o", "  \u001b[1;33m② Evaluation axis for all 19 characters\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[34.3, "o", "    Columbo: \u001b[2maxis: validity of assumptions\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[34.6, "o", "    Picard:  \u001b[2maxis: user experience quality\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[34.9, "o", "    Durden:  \u001b[2maxis: true user demand\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[35.2, "o", "    → Personality + criteria = sharper gaps\r\n\r\n"]
[36.0, "o", "  \u001b[1;31m③ Response obligation\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[36.5, "o", "    When A critiques, B must respond: \u001b[1magree / disagree / defer\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[37.0, "o", "    → One-way drive-bys become two-way arguments\r\n\r\n"]
[37.8, "o", "  \u001b[1;35m④ Six session structures (auto-selected by theme)\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[38.3, "o", "    🗣 Roundtable  ⚖ Tribunal  ⚔ Wargame\r\n"]
[38.8, "o", "    💰 VC Pitch  🏥 Case Conference  🔥 Investigation\r\n"]
[39.5, "o", "    All share a common principle:\r\n"]
[40.0, "o", "      \u001b[1mPhase 1:\u001b[0m Independent context generation\r\n"]
[40.3, "o", "      \u001b[1mPhase 2:\u001b[0m Adversarial dialogue (response required)\r\n"]
[40.6, "o", "      \u001b[1mPhase 3:\u001b[0m Synthesis\r\n\r\n"]
[42.0, "o", "\u001b[1;37m━━━ Before / After ━━━\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[42.5, "o", "  \u001b[2m              v2.4.1              v3.0.0\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[42.8, "o", "  ──────────────────────────────────────────────\r\n"]
[43.1, "o", "  Input         Theme 1 line         Phase 0 auto-collect\r\n"]
[43.4, "o", "  Characters    Personality only      Personality + axis\r\n"]
[43.7, "o", "  Dialogue      One-way critiques     Response obligation\r\n"]
[44.0, "o", "  Structure     Roundtable only       6 structures (auto)\r\n"]
[44.3, "o", "  ──────────────────────────────────────────────\r\n\r\n"]
[45.5, "o", "  \u001b[1mWe DGE'd DGE. It found what we forgot to design.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[46.0, "o", "  \u001b[1mFind what's missing. Turn it into what's needed.\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[47.5, "o", "\u001b[2m  DGE toolkit v3.0.0 · npm: @unlaxer/dge-toolkit · MIT License\u001b[0m\r\n"]
